00:14.597 --> 00:17.475
♪ FOE VS. FRIEND ♪

00:17.559 --> 00:19.853
♪ BRAIN VS. B.O.B. ♪

00:19.936 --> 00:22.814
- ♪ IT'S A SUPER-FREAKY JOB ♪

00:22.897 --> 00:23.565
- OH, YEAH,
IT'S FREAKY.

00:23.648 --> 00:26.067
- ♪<i> MVA</i> ♪

00:26.151 --> 00:28.737
- ♪<i> MONSTERS VS. ALIENS</i> ♪

00:28.820 --> 00:31.489
- [cackles]
- ♪<i> MONSTERS VS. ALIENS</i> ♪

00:31.573 --> 00:33.408
♪<i> MONSTERS VS. ALIENS</i> ♪

00:33.491 --> 00:35.785
♪<i> MVA</i> ♪

00:37.162 --> 00:40.123
[tense music]

00:40.206 --> 00:46.045
♪ ♪

00:46.129 --> 00:48.631
- IT IS INCOMING,
IT IS ON FIRE,

00:48.715 --> 00:52.385
AND IT FEELS NEITHER
REMORSE NOR MERCY.

00:52.469 --> 00:54.304
{\an8}IT IS DODGE BALL,

00:54.387 --> 00:56.806
{\an8}AND SO HELP ME,
I DO LOVE IT.

00:56.890 --> 00:57.807
{\an8}WHOO, HA!

00:57.891 --> 00:59.601
{\an8}THROW YOUR BALL,
DON'T GET HIT,

00:59.684 --> 01:00.977
{\an8}ANYTHING ELSE GOES.

01:01.060 --> 01:03.772
- ANYTHING GOES, YOU SAY?

01:03.855 --> 01:05.147
- NO RULES.

01:05.230 --> 01:07.692
JUST-A THE WAY-A
I LIKE IT.

01:07.776 --> 01:08.985
HOPE YOU WANTED
SOME BIG, RED,

01:09.068 --> 01:11.279
DODGE-BALL-SHAPED TATTOOS
ON YOUR BUTT.

01:11.362 --> 01:14.157
- OH, HO.
THAT SOUNDS AWESOME.

01:14.240 --> 01:15.825
WE SHOULD GET THOSE.

01:15.909 --> 01:17.160
- QUESTION:
IF WE'RE GONNA PLAY

01:17.243 --> 01:19.329
MONSTERS VS. ALIENS
DODGE BALL,

01:19.412 --> 01:20.497
SHOULDN'T THERE BE
A BALL?

01:20.580 --> 01:22.248
- WHAT?
I PUT OUT THREE BALLS

01:22.332 --> 01:23.875
BEFORE I EVEN CALLED YOU
IN HERE.

01:23.958 --> 01:26.377
WHERE DID--
- COMMENCE TREACHERY!

01:28.463 --> 01:31.633
[grunting]

01:31.716 --> 01:32.884
- DODGE.
- HEY.

01:32.967 --> 01:35.595
YOU CAN'T JUST--
WE HADN'T EVEN STARTED YET.

01:35.678 --> 01:37.096
- WE WERE VERY EFFICIENT.

01:37.180 --> 01:41.059
I DREW PICTURES.

01:41.142 --> 01:43.436
- ANYTHING GOES.

01:43.520 --> 01:44.521
- THAT IS INDEED
THE NAME OF THE GAME.

01:44.604 --> 01:47.273
LINK, B.O.B., DOCTOR,
YOU'RE OUT.

01:47.357 --> 01:51.110
- BUTT TATTOO TIME.

01:51.194 --> 01:53.446
- WAIT, I'M LOW PRIORITY?

01:53.530 --> 01:54.989
I'M THE STINKING
TEAM LEADER.

01:55.073 --> 01:57.116
- [grunting]
- OH, NO, YOU--

01:57.200 --> 01:58.493
AH!
OOF!

01:58.576 --> 01:59.244
[grunts]
DANG.

01:59.327 --> 02:01.871
- NOTHING PERSONAL, SUSAN.

02:01.955 --> 02:05.083
WE SIMPLY TOOK OUT
THE REAL THREATS FIRST.

02:05.166 --> 02:07.126
SMARTEST...

02:07.210 --> 02:09.336
- GUILTY.
- STRONGEST...

02:09.419 --> 02:11.965
- YOU GOT
THAT RIGHT, TOES.

02:12.048 --> 02:14.926
- AND MOST UNPREDICTABLE.

02:15.009 --> 02:16.052
- DODGE.

02:16.135 --> 02:18.513
- YOUR ONLY POWER
IS TO MAKE YOURSELF

02:18.596 --> 02:20.598
AN EVEN BIGGER TARGET.

02:20.682 --> 02:23.184
OF COURSE YOU'D BE THE LAST
TO PICK OFF.

02:23.268 --> 02:24.894
- LAST PICK.

02:24.978 --> 02:27.021
- FOR OUR DODGE BALL TEAM'S
LAST PICK,

02:27.105 --> 02:29.190
WE'LL TAKE
THE PRACTICE DUMMY.

02:29.274 --> 02:32.318
- WHAT?
BUT IT CAN'T EVEN DODGE.

02:32.402 --> 02:33.611
- THAT MAKES TWO OF YOU.
HA, HA!

02:33.695 --> 02:36.197
[laughter]

02:36.281 --> 02:38.199
- ELEMENTARY SCHOOL RECESS.

02:38.283 --> 02:40.910
I'VE BEEN
LAST PICK BEFORE.

02:40.994 --> 02:42.662
IT MADE ME ANGRY.

02:42.745 --> 02:44.289
- YES, WELL, THAT'S FASCINATING.

02:44.372 --> 02:47.083
WE'RE GOING TO THROW BALLS
AT YOU NOW.

02:47.167 --> 02:49.127
- BUT YOU KNOW WHAT I DID
WITH THAT ANGER?

02:49.210 --> 02:52.505
I LEARNED TO PLAY
THE HECK OUT OF DODGE BALL.

02:52.589 --> 02:54.966
- [grunts]

02:55.049 --> 03:00.471
- [shouts]
[grunting]

03:02.265 --> 03:02.724
- WOW.
- CHEATER.

03:02.807 --> 03:04.767
I CALL CHEATER.

03:04.851 --> 03:06.144
- TAKES ONE TO KNOW ONE.

03:06.227 --> 03:07.103
- PRECISELY.
I SHOULD KNOW.

03:07.186 --> 03:09.147
- SHE LEFT
THE RAMPAGE ROOM.

03:09.230 --> 03:10.773
SURELY THAT IS OUT-OF-BOUNDS.

03:10.857 --> 03:12.942
- ANYTHING GOES.
[chuckles]

03:13.026 --> 03:14.861
- LET THE HUNT BEGIN.

03:14.944 --> 03:17.947
[shouts]

03:20.783 --> 03:22.327
VORNICARN, COME,
WE MUST DELIVER

03:22.410 --> 03:24.120
A FLAMING BALL OF PAIN.

03:24.203 --> 03:26.456
- I WOULDN'T GET
TOO WORKED UP.

03:26.539 --> 03:28.541
SHE'S ALL BY
HER LONESOME

03:28.625 --> 03:30.585
WITH NO DODGE BALL.

03:30.668 --> 03:34.088
[laughs]

03:34.172 --> 03:35.506
- LAUGH IT UP, BREAD-HEAD.

03:35.590 --> 03:36.841
STORM'S A-COMIN'.

03:36.925 --> 03:38.301
100% CHANCE
OF DODGE BALL,

03:38.384 --> 03:40.011
AND YOU AIN'T GOT
AN UMBRELLA.

03:40.094 --> 03:41.554
- UH, SUZE?

03:41.638 --> 03:43.973
IT'S REALLY FREAKY WHEN
YOU TALK IN THE WALLS LIKE THAT.

03:44.057 --> 03:45.099
- SORRY.

03:45.183 --> 03:46.142
- NEED ANY HELP?
ENEMY INTEL?

03:46.225 --> 03:48.811
MISINFORMATION?
TRASH TALK?

03:48.895 --> 03:50.813
- I'VE BEEN PRACTICING
MY INSULTS.

03:50.897 --> 03:52.357
HEY, IS THAT A HAM,

03:52.440 --> 03:54.025
OR DID YOUR FACE JUST--

03:54.108 --> 03:54.943
WAIT, IT'S PROBABLY
JUST A HAM.

03:55.026 --> 03:57.278
ARE YOU HOLDING A HAM?

03:57.362 --> 03:59.155
AH, HE WAS JUST HOLDING
A HAM.

03:59.238 --> 04:00.448
- WE MAY BE ELIMINATED,

04:00.531 --> 04:01.491
BUT WE ARE STILL
YOUR TEAMMATES.

04:01.574 --> 04:04.327
- RIGHT NOW,
I DON'T HAVE TEAMMATES.

04:04.410 --> 04:06.204
I HAVE A MISSION.

04:06.287 --> 04:08.706
AND THIS TIME,
IT'S PERSONAL.

04:08.790 --> 04:10.083
- BYE, SUSAN!

04:10.166 --> 04:13.962
PLAY SAFE.
WE'LL SAVE YOU SOME HAM.

04:14.045 --> 04:15.755
- BALL AT THE READY, SQWEEP?

04:15.838 --> 04:17.673
AT THE READY.

04:17.757 --> 04:18.841
THERE SHE IS!
FIRE!

04:18.925 --> 04:19.841
- [grunts]

04:19.926 --> 04:21.219
- DEEPEST APOLOGIES.
- YES, YES.

04:21.302 --> 04:23.596
MY MISTAKE--
THERE SHE IS!

04:23.680 --> 04:25.181
- [grunts]

04:25.264 --> 04:28.184
- YET AGAIN, WE ARE VERY SORRY
FOR THIS MISTAKE.

04:28.267 --> 04:31.354
- I CAN'T HELP IT
IF ALL EARTH FEMALES LOOK ALI--

04:31.437 --> 04:32.981
THERE SHE IS!

04:33.064 --> 04:34.482
- [grunts]
OW.

04:34.565 --> 04:36.943
HENRY AIN'T A LADY.

04:37.026 --> 04:38.820
- AND THAT IS WHY
WE DO NOT STRIKE

04:38.903 --> 04:41.406
UNTIL WE HAVE
A CONFIRMED TARGET, VORNICARN.

04:41.489 --> 04:42.782
- [growls]
- HUH? VORNICARN?

04:42.865 --> 04:46.452
- [growls]

04:49.872 --> 04:53.793
- [grunts]

04:53.876 --> 04:55.586
- [screams]

04:55.670 --> 04:57.880
- VORNICARN!

04:57.964 --> 04:58.881
[all gasp]

04:58.965 --> 05:00.550
- [groans]

05:00.633 --> 05:01.050
- WHAT'S GOING--

05:01.134 --> 05:03.094
[chuckles]

05:03.177 --> 05:05.555
SORRY, IT'S JUST--
IT'S KIND OF HILARIOUS.

05:05.638 --> 05:08.599
- "NOW, I HAVE A DODGE BALL.

05:08.683 --> 05:10.768
HA, HA, HA."

05:10.852 --> 05:12.228
- WAY TO GO, SUSAN.

05:12.311 --> 05:13.563
- ONE DOWN,
THREE TO GO.

05:13.646 --> 05:16.733
- YOU HAVE NO WAY OF PROVING
THIS WAS SUSAN.

05:16.816 --> 05:19.902
UH, PERHAPS IT WAS
AN INDUSTRIAL ACCIDENT.

05:19.986 --> 05:22.322
- [grunts]
- "SINCERELY, SUSAN.

05:22.405 --> 05:25.658
'HEART.'
P.S. YOU'RE NEXT."

05:25.742 --> 05:27.493
- VORNICARN, YOU'RE OUT.

05:27.577 --> 05:28.453
- [grunts]
- HEH.

05:28.536 --> 05:30.747
- SOMEONE INSULTED
THE WRONG LADY.

05:30.830 --> 05:32.749
- [screams]

05:32.832 --> 05:36.002
[grunting]

05:36.085 --> 05:37.336
SUSAN.

05:37.420 --> 05:39.255
HEED THE SQUARING
OF STA'ABI.

05:39.338 --> 05:42.008
THIS BALL WILL TASTE
THE FLESH

05:42.091 --> 05:43.801
OF YOUR SOFT EARTH BELLY.

05:43.885 --> 05:46.596
- NUH-UH.

05:46.679 --> 05:48.014
- I KNOW.
WALL TALKIN'.

05:48.097 --> 05:48.639
TOTALLY FREAKY, RIGHT?

05:48.723 --> 05:50.767
[grunts]

05:50.850 --> 05:53.102
- [growls]

05:53.186 --> 05:55.438
[grunting]

05:55.521 --> 05:56.481
[panting]

05:56.564 --> 05:58.357
HA!

05:58.441 --> 05:59.859
AH!

06:01.027 --> 06:02.862
[gasps]
HA.

06:02.945 --> 06:05.281
- [grunts]
NOT A LADY!

06:05.364 --> 06:05.656
- [gasps]

06:05.740 --> 06:08.576
OOH.

06:08.659 --> 06:09.535
[grunts]

06:09.619 --> 06:12.580
[tense music]

06:12.663 --> 06:16.959
♪ ♪

06:17.043 --> 06:20.129
- ♪ WOW, WOW, WHOA ♪

06:20.213 --> 06:23.174
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

06:24.634 --> 06:27.220
- [screams]
- [screams]

06:27.303 --> 06:29.430
[both shouting in slow motion]

06:32.517 --> 06:36.104
AH!
[grunting]

06:36.187 --> 06:38.648
HM.
THE TARGET IS WOUNDED.

06:38.731 --> 06:40.108
GOOD.

06:43.611 --> 06:45.571
- TUESDAY, I MAKE
THE BORSCH.

06:45.655 --> 06:48.533
- [grunts]

06:48.616 --> 06:49.325
- [screams]

06:49.408 --> 06:52.745
- [shouting in slow motion]

06:52.829 --> 06:54.539
- MY BORSCH.

06:58.543 --> 06:59.335
- [grunts]

06:59.418 --> 07:01.420
- STA'ABI, YOU'RE OUT.

07:01.504 --> 07:03.673
[snickers]
I LOVE MY DODGE BALL.

07:03.756 --> 07:04.549
- OOH.

07:04.632 --> 07:07.176
- I'M COMING FOR YOU, COVERTON.

07:07.260 --> 07:08.886
AND DODGE BALL'S
COMING WITH ME.

07:08.970 --> 07:09.846
HUH?

07:09.929 --> 07:12.223
- OH, DEAR.

07:12.306 --> 07:15.935
GUESS WHO'S GOT ALL
THE SPHERICAL PROJECTILE AGAIN.

07:16.018 --> 07:17.895
IN YOUR FACE, SUSAN.

07:17.979 --> 07:21.065
[grunts]

07:21.149 --> 07:23.651
[grunts, sighs]

07:23.734 --> 07:24.819
DO-OVER?
- [growls]

07:24.902 --> 07:27.280
- OH!
- I BELIEVE WE ARE LOSING NOW.

07:27.363 --> 07:28.156
- UNACCEPTABLE.

07:28.239 --> 07:30.491
I REFUSE
TO BE DEFEATED

07:30.575 --> 07:31.367
BY ONE HUMAN WOMAN

07:31.450 --> 07:33.369
WITH A SIMPLE
RUBBER ORB.

07:33.452 --> 07:36.956
OOH.
DEVIOUS IDEA ALERT.

07:37.039 --> 07:38.624
- PROCEED.

07:38.708 --> 07:41.210
- SURELY, A CHILD GENIUS
LIKE YOU

07:41.294 --> 07:42.253
COULD FIND SOME WAY

07:42.336 --> 07:45.173
TO WEAPONIZE
THESE DODGE BALLS.

07:45.256 --> 07:46.591
HM?
- THAT SOUNDS DANGEROUS.

07:46.674 --> 07:49.343
- WELL, THEN I SUPPOSE
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO ADMIT

07:49.427 --> 07:51.888
SHE'S OUTSMARTED US.

07:51.971 --> 07:54.557
- I AM ON IT.

07:54.640 --> 07:56.267
WE REALLY SHOULD DO
A FULL LAB TEST

07:56.350 --> 07:57.810
BEFORE TAKING THESE
INTO THE FIELD.

07:57.894 --> 08:00.146
- NO TIME.
SHE COULD BE ANYWHERE.

08:02.106 --> 08:02.732
- WHOO!

08:02.815 --> 08:05.818
AH!
[grunting]

08:05.902 --> 08:07.403
- AH, SUSAN.

08:07.486 --> 08:10.698
I SEE YOU'VE MET
OUR FIRST MODIFIED DODGE BALL,

08:10.781 --> 08:14.952
A HUMAN-SEEKING MISSILE
I CALL "BASH-SUSAN HUNTER."

08:15.036 --> 08:17.246
[laughs]

08:17.330 --> 08:18.623
- [grunts]
- OH, LOOK.

08:18.706 --> 08:22.293
AND HERE'S HIS TWIN BROTHER
ZIPPY FAST-O.

08:22.376 --> 08:24.962
- AH!
- INCREASED ACCELERATION

08:25.046 --> 08:26.005
WITH EACH IMPACT.

08:26.088 --> 08:28.966
NOT EVEN YOU
CAN DODGE IT FOREVER.

08:29.050 --> 08:30.092
AH! [grunts]
- [laughs]

08:30.176 --> 08:34.096
- [grunts]

08:34.179 --> 08:35.514
- [laughs]

08:35.597 --> 08:36.474
NO!

08:36.557 --> 08:39.936
- I FORFEIT.

08:40.019 --> 08:41.102
AH!
DODGE.

08:41.187 --> 08:42.688
- I DON'T PLAY
FOR FORFEITS.

08:42.772 --> 08:44.607
- SQWEEP, YOU'RE OUT.

08:44.690 --> 08:46.150
NICELY AIMED, SUSAN.

08:46.234 --> 08:47.944
- I AIM
TO MAKE YOU HURT.

08:48.027 --> 08:51.447
- UH, UH, UH, UH.
NOT SO FAST, SUSAN.

08:51.530 --> 08:54.867
YOU'RE STILL HOLDING
MY ULTIMATE BACKUP PLAN.

08:54.951 --> 08:57.703
I CALL HIM
"BOOM, BOOM, WAH!

08:57.787 --> 09:00.498
[mimics explosion]
BYE, BYE."

09:00.581 --> 09:02.124
IF YOU THROW
THAT BALL,

09:02.208 --> 09:05.336
THE ENSUING EXPLOSION
WILL VAPORIZE EVERYTHING

09:05.419 --> 09:07.838
WITHIN A 50-MILE RADIUS.

09:07.922 --> 09:09.757
- COVERTON, YOU MANIAC.

09:09.840 --> 09:11.801
- OH, CALM YOUR ANTENNAE.

09:11.884 --> 09:13.469
SHE'S NOT GOING
TO THROW IT.

09:13.552 --> 09:15.638
SHE HAS NO CHOICE
BUT TO GIVE UP

09:15.721 --> 09:17.640
AND DECLARE ME
THE WINNER.

09:17.723 --> 09:21.852
[laughs]
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, SUSAN?

09:21.936 --> 09:24.105
- BOOM.
- [screams]

09:24.188 --> 09:25.106
- WAIT A MINUTE.

09:25.189 --> 09:26.565
WHEN DID WE GO
FROM CRAZY AWESOME

09:26.649 --> 09:27.233
TO CRAZY <i> CRAZY?</i>

09:27.316 --> 09:30.903
- [groaning, screaming]

09:34.615 --> 09:36.951
[whimpering]

09:37.034 --> 09:38.786
I SURRENDER!
YOU WIN!

09:38.869 --> 09:40.955
IT'S NOT WORTH
EXPLODING OVER.

09:41.038 --> 09:45.376
- I TOLD YOU...
I DON'T PLAY FOR FORFEITS.

09:45.459 --> 09:46.210
- BACK IT DOWN, GINORMICA.

09:46.294 --> 09:48.504
THAT IS AN ORDER.

09:48.587 --> 09:50.006
- TRY AND STOP ME.

09:50.089 --> 09:52.508
- [grunts]

09:52.591 --> 09:55.511
- CURSE YOUR EXPERTLY HONED
DODGING SKILLS.

09:55.594 --> 09:57.722
[grunting]

09:57.805 --> 10:00.016
- SUSAN, I KNOW YOU THINK
THIS WILL HEAL

10:00.099 --> 10:01.726
THE TRAUMA
OF BEING LAST PICK.

10:01.809 --> 10:03.853
BUT WILL IT?
WILL IT REALLY?

10:03.936 --> 10:05.104
- YES.
- WOW!

10:05.187 --> 10:08.441
THAT'S GREAT.
YOU GO RIGHT AHEAD THEN, SISTER.

10:08.524 --> 10:11.444
- STOP HER,
YOU MINDLESS GOO-BAG!

10:17.533 --> 10:18.701
- [grunts in slow motion]

10:20.953 --> 10:22.788
- [screams in slow motion]

10:28.627 --> 10:31.130
- WHO'S LAST PICK NOW, CHUMP?

10:31.213 --> 10:32.256
- COVERTON, YOU'RE OUT!

10:32.340 --> 10:35.217
VICTORY, TEAM MONSTER,
BUT MOSTLY SUSAN.

10:35.301 --> 10:38.554
- WHAT?
BUT--BUT SHE CAN'T DO THAT.

10:38.637 --> 10:41.724
THAT WAS AN EYEBALL.

10:41.807 --> 10:46.937
- ANYTHING GOES.
[mimics record scratching]

10:48.898 --> 10:50.066
- [belches]

10:50.149 --> 10:52.068
- SORRY, B.O.B.
I NEEDED A LOANER.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.235
FORGIVE ME?
- YOU MONSTER.

10:53.319 --> 10:56.280
[grunts]
WAIT, SORRY.

10:56.364 --> 10:58.657
MIXING UP WORDS AGAIN.
YOU THE MONSTER.

10:58.741 --> 11:01.494
YEAH.
GO, SUSAN.

11:01.577 --> 11:04.413
[Beethoven's
<i>Symphony No. 9</i> playing]

11:04.497 --> 11:10.044
♪ ♪

11:11.379 --> 11:15.091
[tense music]

11:15.174 --> 11:21.472
♪ ♪

11:21.555 --> 11:24.600
{\an8}- [humming]

11:24.683 --> 11:26.435
{\an8}[grunts]
-<i> LA CUCARACHA</i> IS DOWN.

11:26.519 --> 11:28.521
{\an8}SECURE THE AREA.

11:32.775 --> 11:34.777
AREA SECURED.
SEND IN WHINER BABY.

11:34.860 --> 11:38.239
- GUYS, I TOLD YOU
I HATE THAT CODE NAME.

11:38.322 --> 11:40.449
- EXCUSE ME,
BUT COULD SOMEONE EXPLAIN

11:40.533 --> 11:42.451
WHY MY LOWER THORAX
IS BEING CRUSHED?

11:42.535 --> 11:43.619
- SORRY.
- LEAVE US.

11:43.702 --> 11:46.163
- YOU HEARD WHINER BABY.
ROLL OUT.

11:48.791 --> 11:50.626
- NOBODY RESPECTS MY AUTHORITY.

11:50.709 --> 11:51.419
- AN ODD STATEMENT,
MR. PRESIDENT,

11:51.502 --> 11:53.629
CONSIDERING YOU ARE--

11:53.712 --> 11:55.631
WELL, YOU ARE THE PRESIDENT.

11:55.714 --> 11:56.632
- [grunts]
IT DOESN'T MEAN WHAT IT USED TO.

11:56.715 --> 11:58.384
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
MY TYPICAL DAY IS LIKE?

11:58.467 --> 11:59.885
LISTEN UP, MR. SPEAKER.

11:59.969 --> 12:03.431
IT'S MY WAY OR THE--HELLO?
[dial tone]

12:03.514 --> 12:04.807
MARGARET, COFFEE.
- NOT MY JOB, SIR.

12:04.890 --> 12:07.935
GET YOUR OWN.
- NO, IKE--NO, OUTSIDE.

12:08.018 --> 12:08.686
[dog barking]
OH.

12:08.769 --> 12:11.605
BAD DOG.
VERY BAD DOG.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.482
MARGARET!
- PICK IT UP YOURSELF, SIR.

12:13.566 --> 12:14.942
- [sighs]

12:15.025 --> 12:17.987
NOBODY PAYS ATTENTION TO ME.

12:18.070 --> 12:19.613
- WHA--WERE YOU SAYING
SOMETHING?

12:19.697 --> 12:21.365
- DOCTOR, THIS IS A CRISIS.

12:21.449 --> 12:22.658
I NEED TO ASK THE COUNTRY

12:22.741 --> 12:24.493
TO MAKE
SOME HARD SACRIFICES,

12:24.577 --> 12:25.494
AND I'M JUST
NOT AUTHORITATIVE ENOUGH.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.746
GIVE ME SOME AUTHORITY.

12:27.830 --> 12:31.125
MAKE PEOPLE DO
WHAT I SAY.

12:31.208 --> 12:32.293
- [laughs evilly]

12:32.376 --> 12:35.004
- ANYBODY SEE MY mePOD?

12:35.087 --> 12:36.338
I CAN'T REMEMBER
WHERE I PLUGGED IT IN.

12:36.422 --> 12:37.506
- SHH.
PRESIDENT IS TALKING.

12:37.590 --> 12:40.593
- SO, MY FELLOW AMERICANS,

12:40.676 --> 12:42.678
TODAY, I AM ASKING YOU

12:42.761 --> 12:44.805
TO CUT BACK
ON THE FRENCH FRIES.

12:44.889 --> 12:46.765
SERIOUSLY, YOU REALLY
DON'T NEED THEM WITH EVERY MEAL.

12:46.849 --> 12:49.477
- YES, SIR.
- THIS IS WEIRD.

12:49.560 --> 12:51.645
USUALLY, THE PRESIDENT'S SPEECH
IS JUST SO BORING,

12:51.729 --> 12:53.564
I--
[snores]

12:53.647 --> 12:55.524
[grunts]
SORRY, I FELL ASLEEP

12:55.608 --> 12:56.817
JUST THINKING ABOUT THEM.
- I KNOW.

12:56.901 --> 12:58.861
BUT THIS TIME, THERE WAS
SOMETHING ABOUT THE PRESIDENT,

12:58.944 --> 13:01.197
LIKE--LIKE HE EXUDED
THIS--THIS--

13:01.280 --> 13:03.282
- AUTHORITY?
- YES, EXACTLY.

13:03.365 --> 13:04.533
I WANTED TO DO
WHATEVER HE SAID.

13:04.617 --> 13:06.035
- [laughs evilly]
- DR. C.

13:06.118 --> 13:09.079
YOU'RE LAUGHING IN AN
I-DID-SOMETHING-MAD-SCIENCE-Y

13:09.163 --> 13:10.247
KIND OF WAY.

13:10.331 --> 13:12.708
- I MAY HAVE HELPED
THE PRESIDENT A WEE BIT.

13:12.791 --> 13:14.418
- UH-OH.
- YOU SEE, I GAVE HIM

13:14.502 --> 13:17.421
THE AIR OF AUTHORITY.

13:17.505 --> 13:20.382
[laughs]

13:20.466 --> 13:21.717
- THE AIR OF AUTHORITY?

13:21.800 --> 13:24.094
- A DELICATE COLOGNE
WITH HINTS OF SANDALWOOD SPICE

13:24.178 --> 13:25.596
AND THE ABILITY
TO MAKE EVERYONE DO

13:25.679 --> 13:27.223
EXACTLY WHAT YOU SAY.

13:27.306 --> 13:28.557
- YOU DIDN'T.
- I DID.

13:28.641 --> 13:32.061
BUT WORRY NOT, SUSAN, THE EFFECT
LASTS BUT A FEW HOURS.

13:32.144 --> 13:33.979
- I SWEAR,
AM I THE ONLY PERSON AROUND HERE

13:34.063 --> 13:35.481
WITH ANY SENSE
OF RESPONSIBILITY?

13:35.564 --> 13:37.900
- WHAT?
[grunts]

13:37.983 --> 13:39.026
- NOBODY SHOULD HAVE
THAT KIND OF POWER.

13:39.109 --> 13:41.946
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.
- BUT, SUSAN--

13:42.029 --> 13:43.155
- YOU KNOW I'M RIGHT.

13:43.239 --> 13:44.698
LOCK THAT AUTHORITY STUFF UP
FOR GOOD.

13:44.782 --> 13:46.242
IF IT FELL INTO
THE WRONG HANDS,

13:46.325 --> 13:46.992
WHO KNOWS
WHAT COULD HAPPEN?

13:47.076 --> 13:49.286
- OH, I HAVE A FEW IDEAS.

13:49.370 --> 13:52.164
[laughs]

13:52.248 --> 13:56.502
UM, HELLO?

13:56.585 --> 14:01.090
YOUR SHRINK RAY STINKS.

14:01.173 --> 14:04.927
- [snoring]

14:07.012 --> 14:09.640
- HUSH MODE.
- ACTIVATING HUSH MODE!

14:09.723 --> 14:10.516
NOW!
- [screams]

14:10.599 --> 14:12.518
- [grunts]
WHAT?

14:12.601 --> 14:14.520
- SHH.

14:14.603 --> 14:16.897
- [snores]

14:18.274 --> 14:20.985
- AT LAST.
THE AIR OF AUTHORITY.

14:26.407 --> 14:28.200
- YO, COVERTON.
- OH, NO.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.451
B.O.B.!

14:29.535 --> 14:31.787
- UH, HAVE YOU SEEN
MY mePOD?

14:31.870 --> 14:33.205
I PLUGGED IT IN SOMEWHERE.

14:33.289 --> 14:34.707
I JUST CAN'T REMEMBER WHERE.

14:34.790 --> 14:36.166
OH, HEY, CHECK IT.
I'M LIKE A FIREFLY'S BUTT.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.210
[laughs]

14:38.294 --> 14:39.628
- WHAT'S ALL THE NOISE?

14:39.712 --> 14:41.630
COVERTON, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

14:41.714 --> 14:43.632
- YOU WERE UP
TO SOMETHING SNEAKY.

14:43.716 --> 14:45.467
YOU GOT THAT SNEAKY LOOK
ON YOUR FACE...

14:45.551 --> 14:48.137
- MM.
- AND YOUR FEET.

14:48.220 --> 14:49.847
SEE IT? SNEAKY.
- [gasps]

14:49.930 --> 14:52.641
THE AIR OF AUTHORITY
IS MISSING.

14:52.725 --> 14:53.517
- YOU WEASELLY HOVER JERK.

14:53.601 --> 14:55.561
- NO, NO, NO, NO.

14:55.644 --> 14:57.229
NO, I WAS JUST
DOING SOMETHING

14:57.313 --> 14:59.982
EXTREMELY INNOCENT
THAT I WILL THINK OF

15:00.065 --> 15:02.067
IF YOU GIVE ME A MOMENT.

15:02.151 --> 15:04.862
- GUYS, BASED ON
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING,

15:04.945 --> 15:06.655
I FEEL WE SHOULD
BELIEVE COVERTON.

15:06.739 --> 15:09.533
- I--YOU DO?

15:09.617 --> 15:10.659
- GEE, B.O.B,
NOW THAT YOU SAY IT,

15:10.743 --> 15:12.828
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:12.911 --> 15:14.538
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

15:14.622 --> 15:16.665
MY FIRST INSTINCT
WAS TO LAUNCH COVERTON

15:16.749 --> 15:19.001
BACK INTO SPACE
WITH MY TWIN BOOSTER ROCKETS,

15:19.084 --> 15:21.462
SHA-BING AND SHA-BANG.
MWAH.

15:21.545 --> 15:23.172
BUT THEN, I LISTENED
TO WHAT B.O.B HAD TO SAY

15:23.255 --> 15:24.965
AND REALIZED,
"WOW, I NEED TO LEARN TO TRUST."

15:25.049 --> 15:28.469
- B.O.B. IS AFTER ALL
THE AUTHORITY

15:28.552 --> 15:29.970
ON THE SUBJECT
OF COVERTON.

15:30.054 --> 15:32.139
- AND REALLY
ALL SUBJECTS, RIGHT?

15:32.222 --> 15:33.641
- OH, YEAH.
TOTALLY.

15:33.724 --> 15:34.892
- WAIT.

15:34.975 --> 15:37.561
IS THE AIR OF AUTHORITY
AFFECTING ME?

15:37.645 --> 15:39.104
[sniffing]

15:39.188 --> 15:41.565
B.O.B., TELL US
TO DO SOMETHING.

15:41.649 --> 15:43.984
- OKAY.
MAKE FUNNY NOISES.

15:44.068 --> 15:45.527
[Susan, Link, and Doc
make funny noises]

15:45.611 --> 15:48.447
- OH, FASCINATING.

15:48.530 --> 15:50.824
- YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
IS FASCINATING?

15:50.908 --> 15:51.742
CAKE.

15:51.825 --> 15:52.951
- ME LIKEY CAKE.
- YES!

15:53.035 --> 15:54.036
- I'M ENTHRALLED
BY FROSTED BAKED GOODS.

15:54.119 --> 15:56.246
- I ALSO LIKE HATS.

15:56.330 --> 15:58.374
HEY, WOULDN'T IT
BE GREAT

15:58.457 --> 15:59.958
IF THERE WERE CAKE HATS?

16:00.042 --> 16:01.460
[gasps]
LET'S GO MAKE SOME.

16:01.543 --> 16:02.920
- GENIUS.

16:03.003 --> 16:06.507
- MM, NOT AT ALL
WHAT I HAD PLANNED,

16:06.590 --> 16:08.842
BUT IT'LL WORK.

16:08.926 --> 16:12.471
[upbeat music]

16:12.554 --> 16:15.224
- WHAT THE DING-DONG-DIDDLY
ARE YOU PEOPLE DOING?

16:15.307 --> 16:16.725
- THE CONGA.

16:16.809 --> 16:19.144
- AND JUST WHY ARE YOU WASTING
TAXPAYER DOLLARS

16:19.228 --> 16:21.063
ON CAKE HATS
AND LATIN DANCE?

16:21.146 --> 16:22.481
- B.O.B. TOLD US TO.

16:22.564 --> 16:24.400
- I DID.

16:24.483 --> 16:26.568
- SOUNDS LIKE A FINE IDEA
TO ME.

16:26.652 --> 16:31.782
[cheering]

16:31.865 --> 16:34.368
- I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M NOT AFFECTED.

16:34.451 --> 16:38.414
MY GENETICALLY SUPERIOR
TELEKINETIC BRAIN, I SUPPOSE.

16:38.497 --> 16:40.249
[chuckles]

16:40.332 --> 16:42.209
MM, POINT IS
THEY'RE ALL LISTENING

16:42.292 --> 16:44.128
TO THE IDIOT,
AND THE IDIOT

16:44.211 --> 16:45.462
LISTENS TO ME.

16:45.546 --> 16:46.880
I CAN'T THINK OF
A BETTER OPPORTUNITY

16:46.964 --> 16:50.467
TO BRING EARTH
TO ITS KNEES.

16:50.551 --> 16:52.052
[screams]

16:52.136 --> 16:53.429
COVERTON DOWN!

16:53.512 --> 16:55.305
both: HUG.

16:55.389 --> 16:56.765
- COME ON.
BRING IT IN.

16:56.849 --> 16:57.766
all: HUG.

16:57.850 --> 16:59.518
- I LOVE HUG TIME.

16:59.601 --> 17:01.729
- B.O.B., CHECK IT OUT.

17:01.812 --> 17:03.397
I PAINTED A FLOWER
JUST LIKE YOU SAID.

17:03.480 --> 17:04.440
- SUSAN, THAT'S NICE.

17:04.522 --> 17:06.275
I WANT TO ACKNOWLEDGE
THE EFFORT,

17:06.358 --> 17:08.694
BUT WHEN I SAID
YOU SHOULD PAINT FLOWERS,

17:08.777 --> 17:11.363
I MEANT YOU SHOULD
PAINT FLOWERS.

17:11.446 --> 17:14.742
SEE?
- AND NOW, COVERTON STRIKES.

17:14.825 --> 17:15.617
- HERE'S A HUG.
- [grunts]

17:15.701 --> 17:18.119
[shouts]
- [grunts]

17:18.203 --> 17:19.788
- OOH, SAY, B.O.B.

17:19.872 --> 17:21.623
YOU KNOW WHAT GOES GREAT
WITH CAKE?

17:21.707 --> 17:22.958
ICE CREAM.

17:23.040 --> 17:25.627
MIGHT I SUGGEST
AN ICE CREAM SOCIAL

17:25.711 --> 17:28.130
IN THE MESS HALL?

17:28.213 --> 17:31.842
- HM, I MEAN, YEAH,
THE WHOLE ICE CREAM SOCIAL THING

17:31.925 --> 17:34.011
IS KIND OF OLD-TIMEY,
BUT LET ME

17:34.094 --> 17:36.805
PUT MY SPECIAL
B.O.B. SPIN ON THIS.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.432
HEY, EVERYBODY.

17:38.515 --> 17:40.100
B.O.B. HERE.

17:40.184 --> 17:43.145
MEET AT THE MESS HALL
AT OH-RIGHT-NOW-HUNDRED HOURS

17:43.228 --> 17:46.523
FOR A FISH AND SOUR CREAM
SOCIAL.

17:46.607 --> 17:49.485
all: YAY!
[overlapping chatter]

17:49.568 --> 17:50.611
- YOU COMING, BUDDY?

17:50.694 --> 17:55.866
- I'LL BE ALONG
MOMENTARILY, BUDDY.

17:55.949 --> 17:57.993
SOMETIMES, IT'S JUST
TOO EASY.

17:58.076 --> 18:01.747
AND NOW,
FOR MY FAVORITE TUNE,

18:01.830 --> 18:04.541
"POWER CORE MELTDOWN."

18:06.585 --> 18:10.172
AH, HA!

18:10.255 --> 18:12.424
[alarm blaring]

18:12.508 --> 18:15.552
- WARNING: POWER CORE
HAS BECOME UNSTABLE.

18:15.636 --> 18:17.429
T-MINUS TEN MINUTES
TO CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION.

18:17.513 --> 18:21.308
- THAT COULD BURN A HOLE
RIGHT THROUGH THE EARTH'S CRUST.

18:21.391 --> 18:23.101
- AND DESTROY ALL LIFE
ON YOUR PLANET.

18:23.185 --> 18:24.603
- WHAT SHOULD WE DO, B.O.B?

18:24.686 --> 18:28.398
- I SAY WE PRETEND
IT'S NOT HAPPENING

18:28.482 --> 18:29.441
AND HOPE IT GOES AWAY.

18:29.525 --> 18:31.193
all: YAY!

18:31.276 --> 18:32.945
- [laughs evilly]

18:33.028 --> 18:34.696
- T-MINUS EIGHT MINUTES
TO CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION.

18:34.780 --> 18:37.741
- NOT FOR COVERTON.

18:37.825 --> 18:39.326
BUH-BYE, EARTH.

18:39.409 --> 18:40.536
[laughs evilly]

18:40.619 --> 18:42.287
ESCAPE POD, ACTIVATE.

18:42.371 --> 18:44.498
INITIATE LAUNCH SEQUENCE.

18:44.581 --> 18:46.333
OH, AND FOR
MY IN-FLIGHT MEAL,

18:46.416 --> 18:49.211
LET'S GO WITH A GOBLET
OF BLATOXINAL JUICE

18:49.294 --> 18:51.713
AND SEARED GURGLE BEAST.

18:51.797 --> 18:54.049
[grunts]
- UNABLE TO COMPLY.

18:54.132 --> 18:56.468
- WHAT? IS THE GURGLE BEAST
NOT FRESH?

18:56.552 --> 19:00.222
- NO POWER.
SHUTTING DOWN.

19:00.305 --> 19:01.431
- HOW CAN IT NOT
HAVE POWER?

19:01.515 --> 19:03.851
I ALWAYS KEEP IT
PLUGGED IN.

19:03.934 --> 19:06.144
"CHARGING mePOD.

19:06.228 --> 19:08.438
DOO NOT UN-PLOOG."

19:08.522 --> 19:10.440
B.O.B.!

19:10.524 --> 19:12.401
- WARNING:
T-MINUS SEVEN MINUTES

19:12.484 --> 19:13.902
TO CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION.

19:13.986 --> 19:14.611
- AH!

19:14.695 --> 19:18.407
[screaming]

19:18.490 --> 19:20.701
FLOOG-NOG!
IT'S NOT WORKING.

19:20.784 --> 19:22.786
SOMEONE IS GOING TO
HAVE TO ACTUALLY GO

19:22.870 --> 19:25.706
INTO THE CORE
AND RE-ROUTE THE POWER COILS.

19:25.789 --> 19:28.542
AND THAT SOMEONE
HAS TO BE...

19:28.625 --> 19:30.419
DR. COCKROACH,
YOU MUST SAVE US.

19:30.502 --> 19:32.754
- SORRY, B.O.B. TOLD ME
TO PRETEND IT'S NOT HAPPENING

19:32.838 --> 19:35.132
AND HOPE IT GOES AWAY.

19:35.215 --> 19:35.924
A MOST SENSIBLE PLAN.

19:36.008 --> 19:39.011
- YOU, PREHISTORIC FISH-MAN.

19:39.094 --> 19:39.928
SURELY, YOU WILL SAVE US.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.431
- WHO AM I GOING
TO LISTEN TO?

19:42.514 --> 19:44.558
MY AUTHORITATIVE BLUE BUD
OR YOU?

19:44.641 --> 19:46.977
DUDE, YOU'RE NOT EVEN WEARING
A CAKE HAT.

19:47.060 --> 19:50.230
- B.O.B., PLEASE,
I BEG YOU,

19:50.314 --> 19:52.399
TELL THEM TO FIX
THE POWER CORE.

19:52.482 --> 19:54.776
- COVERTON, BUDDY,
YOU LOOK TENSE.

19:54.860 --> 19:55.652
DIG IN.
- MM.

19:55.736 --> 19:57.821
IT DOES LOOK
RATHER TASTY--

19:57.905 --> 19:59.781
NO!
MUST SAVE COVERTON!

19:59.865 --> 20:01.033
[cries]
- WARNING.

20:01.116 --> 20:04.036
T-MINUS FOUR MINUTES
TO CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION.

20:04.119 --> 20:06.413
- OH, THAT DOESN'T LOOK FUN
AT ALL.

20:08.999 --> 20:10.500
[gasps]

20:10.584 --> 20:12.586
OH.
[grunts]

20:12.669 --> 20:14.671
- T-MINUS THREE MINUTES
TO CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION.

20:14.755 --> 20:17.716
[grunting]

20:17.799 --> 20:20.886
[screaming]

20:20.969 --> 20:22.221
IT BURNS!

20:22.304 --> 20:23.430
- HERE'S ANOTHER THOUGHT
I HAD.

20:23.513 --> 20:27.184
[high-pitched]
WHAT IF WE ALL TALK LIKE THIS?

20:27.267 --> 20:28.977
- [high-pitched] WELL,
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA, B.O.B.,

20:29.061 --> 20:31.188
BUT...
[coughs, clears throat]

20:31.271 --> 20:32.773
[normal voice]
I CAN'T DO IT.

20:32.856 --> 20:36.318
DON'T HATE, EVERYBODY,
BUT SEEMS KINDA DUMB?

20:36.401 --> 20:38.862
NO OFFENSE, B.O.B.
- OH, NONE TAKEN.

20:38.946 --> 20:40.948
- ALL RIGHT, SINCE WE'RE
SPEAKING OUR MINDS,

20:41.031 --> 20:42.741
I'VE BEEN GETTING CRUMBS
IN MY HAIR ALL DAY,

20:42.824 --> 20:44.326
AND IT'S STARTING
TO MAKE ME CRAZY.

20:44.409 --> 20:47.162
- GUYS, WELL, WHY DIDN'T
YOU SAY SO BEFORE?

20:47.245 --> 20:49.081
- WELL, YOU SEEMED
SO AUTHORITATIVE AND--

20:49.164 --> 20:51.583
[gasps]
IT WAS THE AIR OF AUTHORITY.

20:51.667 --> 20:53.752
THANK GOODNESS THE EFFECTS
ARE ONLY TEMPORARY.

20:53.835 --> 20:54.795
- THE AIR OF WHAT NOW?

20:54.878 --> 20:57.464
DOCTOR, WAS I PRANCING
AND HUGGING

20:57.547 --> 20:59.675
AND WEARING A DUMB CAKE
ON MY NOGGIN

20:59.758 --> 21:01.677
'CAUSE OF SOME LAME-BRAINED
INVENTION OF YOURS?

21:01.760 --> 21:03.011
- WELL, I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'D CALL

21:03.095 --> 21:05.180
A HIGH-END FRAGRANCE
AN INVENTION, BUT--

21:05.263 --> 21:08.475
- WARNING: T-MINUS ONE MINUTE
TO CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION.

21:08.558 --> 21:10.269
- THIS IS NOT OUR TOP CONCERN
AT THE MOMENT.

21:10.352 --> 21:12.229
SOMEONE NEEDS TO GET
INTO THE CORE AND RE-ROUTE--

21:12.312 --> 21:14.439
- NEVER MIND.
- MY TOES.

21:14.523 --> 21:16.149
MY PRECIOUS TOES.
- SOMEONE'S ALREADY DOING IT.

21:16.233 --> 21:19.695
- CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION
IN FIVE, FOUR,

21:19.778 --> 21:23.699
THREE, TWO...

21:23.782 --> 21:27.494
CATASTROPHIC IMPLOSION AVERTED.

21:27.577 --> 21:29.162
- SO TENDER.

21:29.246 --> 21:32.249
SO VERY, VERY RAW.

21:32.332 --> 21:33.375
- COVERTON.

21:33.458 --> 21:34.876
- ALL THIS TIME,
I THOUGHT YOU WANTED

21:34.960 --> 21:36.294
TO DESTROY THE EARTH,
AND HERE YOU ARE SAVING IT.

21:36.378 --> 21:40.048
WAY TO GO.
- UP HIGH, ALIEN GUY.

21:40.132 --> 21:41.508
- WELL DONE, SIR.

21:41.591 --> 21:42.884
- ALL RIGHT.

21:42.968 --> 21:45.637
- [screams, groans]
